Description:
All You Could Ever Want On 1/2 An Acre!
Situated in a peaceful and private location on a park like setting of approximately 1/2 an acre is this meticulously maintained family home that has plenty of room for even the largest of families. The home features a very functional floorplan that has been designed to ensure everyone has their own space .Boasting
5 bedrooms, multiple living areas including a formal lounge and dining room with feature open fireplace, family and meals area that is overlooked by the stunning kitchen with 900ml stainless steel oven, stainless steel dishwasher and stone benchtops. Special features include high ceilings, polished timber floors, air conditioner, coonara, gas ducted heating, picture windows and two quality bathrooms. Outside there's plenty of space to entertain and enjoy the country atmosphere with a covered decked entertaining area, sweeping verandas, outdoor covered pool, large levelled grass areas for your kids and four legged friends to play,

Description:
Lovingly Maintained Family Home!
This lovely house on quarter of an acre has been lovingly maintained inside and out. The front garden has stacked stone pillars and picket fence, manicured front lawn and the front of the house has character which is inviting. The inside has been updated with a contemporary kitchen with stone bench tops, glass splash back, stainless steel gas cooking, integrated dishwasher and loads of cupboards. The kitchen adjoins the open plan meals and ample living area. There are floorboards throughout the living areas and are polished giving the home a warm feel and the carpet in the bedrooms is soft underfoot. There are three good sized bedrooms with built in robes, the master having a huge walk in robe and new ensuite. There is also a study or perhaps nursery adjoining this area. There is a family bathroom with separate toilet, laundry with ample storage and access to the undercover rear entertaining area. For those who like to grow their own vegies there is a fantastic vegie patch which is fenced off to keep the pesky rabbits away and there is plenty of space for the kids to run around on the back lawn. There is also a great big garden shed which could have a myriad of uses. This home leaves you nothing to do but enjoy, come and have a look!

Start Building On This Fabulous 1 Acre Block...Site Already Cut!
Hurry - this is the one you have been looking for! Cleared & boasting a peaceful outlook, this block already has a house site cut, driveway & has 3 phase electricity, gas, water & phone already connected (to house site) plus there is a sewerage treatment plant already to go! Fully fenced, this position offers easy access to Emerald, Cockatoo & Pakenham & provides a peaceful lifestyle with privacy away from neighbours - call us & get your plans started today!
Cockatoo
Cockatoo is a town in Victoria, 48 km south-east of Melbourne's central business district. Its local government area is the Shire of Cardinia. Cockatoo is named after Cockatoo Creek, which runs through the town, and which the town was previously named.
Cockatoo's small commercial centre is located along a steep section of McBride Street and includes a small supermarket and a selection of cafes and other places to eat. The Puffing Billy tourist railway line crosses right next to the shops at the base of McBride Street, recreating those days of stream train travel from long ago as it regularly passes through the town centre.
Cockatoo has a good selection of sporting facilities. In the town centre along the west side of Pakenham Road is a bowling club, basketball courts, tennis courts and other recreational facilities. The Cockatoo Sports Complex is located in Mountain Road and consists of an indoor stadium, oval, athletics track and netball courts.

Description:
CONTEMPORARY COMFORT IN A SERENE SETTING
Nestled onto a flat, clear block with landscaped gardens and plenty of room to move this superb family home has been lovingly updated and maintained to provide exceptional comfort and convenience. The kitchen and bathroom have been tastefully renovated with quality fittings and finishes providing a chic, modern feel. Split system cooling, ducted heating and a wood heater maintain a cozy ambience in any season. The home is fully insulated with recently added plaster ceilings and fresh paint. The large living area includes a bar and views across the front yard and into the trees where Puffing Billy can be seen on its regular journey through Cockatoo. Outside you'll discover a covered barbecue area, a handy storage shed and a double carport with direct access to the home. There is plenty of off street parking for more vehicles including a boat or caravan or tradies truck or trailer. The 2.5kW solar electricity system includes a 3.5kW inverter should the lucky buyer wish to reduce their power bills even further. The shops, restaurants and cafes of central Cockatoo are a short stroll away adding another tick to an already impressive list of features. What a stunner!

Solid Brick Home on Half an Acre!
They dont build them like this anymore! This lovely solid brick home on a corner block is conveniently located within walking distance to Cockatoo Primary School & Shops. As you drive through the large front gates youll notice that the home is a quality construction with a 3 car pitched roof carport & established front garden ensuring your privacy. Inside the home there are 3 bedrooms, a family bathroom with separate toilet, a large laundry with lots of cupboards & a timber kitchen with gas cooktop which opens onto the meals area & big family room with toasty open fire. The third bedroom is huge with its own entrance, a great space for teenagers or maybe a home office. Features include mains gas ducted heating, split system cooling, hardwood floors & quality window furnishings. Outside there is a huge entertaining area & the rear yard is terraced with stone work & has steps leading to the gorgeous planned gardens with many native shrubs, flowers & roses & a handy garden storage shed. This home is located in a private, quiet area & has previously yielded a great rental price. Inspection wont disappoint.
